<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-709-932  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 709 932.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  August 6 1990 n312 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wang: '91 will be profitable. (Wang Laboratories Inc. reports 4thqtr fiscal 1990 losses of $500 million)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chester, John S. Jr.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Wang Laboratories Inc reports 4th qtr fiscal 1990 losses of nearly$500 million, including one-time charges of $417.4 million accruedby a streamlining and reorganization program ordered by RichardMiller, the company's CEO and chairman.andP;  Revenue for the period isreported at $652.2 million, down from $750.9 million in theprevious year's 4th qtr.andP;  Wang has not made a profit since fiscal1988, and suffered a 1990 total operating loss of $715.9 million.andO;The company's stock value has fallen to less than half of its late1988 value.andP;  The market shift away from second-tier proprietarycomputer systems toward Unix and open-architecture technologiesmay hamper Wang's efforts to boost revenues.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wang Laboratories Inc. (finance).andO;Ticker:    WANC.andO;Topic:     LossesFourth QuarterFinancial StabilityBusiness PlanningProprietary SystemsStockForecastingRevenue.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Market nosedive. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>